> Hi Dan,
> Install a thermostat if carburetored.  If you have
> the complete engine with 
> Mexi FI which helps control oil temp via leaning out
> the fuel mixture and 
> sensing this with temp sensors.  Plus as you say
> much of Mexico does not get
> 
> as cold as the USA does.  Also the flaps help to aim
> cooling air to the 
> proper places and if you ever leave you state and
> end up in weather lower 
> than 70F the thermostat will help keep your engine
> happy and keep you warmer
> 
> with more heat exchanger output.  Especially since
> you Floridians tend to 
> freeze once the outside temps drop below 70F!  ;-)
